			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2022</a> keynote:</span><br><i>People Do Not Want to Learn a New Language But a New Library</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/ShigeruChiba.html">Shigeru Chiba</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/3567512.3571831">10.1145/3567512.3571831</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t6d.html"><span class="tagM">T6D: Synergies</span></a><ul><li> Keynote that frames a broader agenda about language-like libraries and embedded DSLs.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3c.html"><span class="tagL">T3C: DSLs</span></a><ul><li> It discusses embedded domain-specific languages as a practical alternative to standalone languages.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1d.html"><span class="tagL">T1D: Composition</span></a><ul><li> It emphasizes embedding/composition of language concepts inside host languages and libraries.
</li></ul></li></ul>
